    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Monica Carrillo",
          "underline": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Monica Carrillo Zegarra is a journalist, poet, artist, and activist whose work engages deeply with themes of race, gender, and Afro-Peruvian identity. She is the founder of LUNDU, an Afro-Peruvian organization that advocates for Afro-Peruvian human rights, with a particular focus on Black women and Youth. Her antiracist fight has also been visible in her advocacy work for removing Black face characters from the Peruvian national TV, which repeats colonial and racist stereotypes about Blackness. "
        }
      ]
    },
